parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the rear axle differential can cause the vehicle to vibrate, make loud noises, and potentially seize, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to become stuck in neutral or park, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power and die without warning, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power and dies without warning
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the fuel pump makes a loud noise or whining sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the fuel tank or fuel injectors can cause fuel to spill onto the tires or brakes, increasing the risk of fires or explosions, especially in the event of a rear-end collision.
symptoms: Fuel leaks or spills from the fuel tank or fuel injectors

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the fuel tank may increase the risk of fuel tank rupture or explosion in the event of a rear-end collision, which can lead to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: as this issue is related to the design of the fuel tank rather than a specific failure or malfunction.
